In Mingling
This part compares the e f fects of mingling plantations of fir and one broadleaf species stands on soil carbon fixation capacity with those of pure fi r . Chinese fir trees are mostly planted in western Hunan Province as an economically ef - ficient timber species. Howeve r , fir trees need to absorb much nitrogen and phosphorus nutrients from the soil during the growth process, triggering a large amount of SOC decomposition. Experiments show that while managing the Chinese fir plantation, the mixture with 20% macclure michelia leads to a greater SOC fixation capacity and better growth of the plantation.

In Macro
Overall, the forest carbon fixation capacity in Hunan Province has been steadily increasing, and soil shows absolute advantages in carbon fixation capacity compared with plants. Especially western Hunan and southern Hunan have rich forest resources and relatively high forest management levels, maintaining leading carbon fixation capacity and carbon storage level. Howeve r , the level of science and technology and economic development in the western and southern regions is relatively backward compared with other areas of Hunan Province.
